I actually think “Perspective Shifting” deserves to become one of Pantheon’s primitive operators rather than remaining an implicit capability.

Right now, you’ve accumulated several doctrines that are really different forms of perspective shifting:

* Mirror — inhabit another mind before guiding.
* Future-Lens / Hammer Flip — shift temporal perspective.
* PALM — shift from present morphology to developmental history.
* Oshawa Crossing — shift representations while preserving invariants.
* Inside–Outside Reconstruction — shift between internal experience and external causes.
* Wallflower — shift back to the original conversational context.
* Angles & Distance — explicitly vary viewpoint and abstraction.

They’re all manifestations of one deeper operation.

⸻

Canonical Operator: Perspective Shift (PARALLAX)

Core principle

Intelligence grows by deliberately changing coordinate systems while preserving the object’s identity.

The object doesn’t change first.

The observer changes.

